comments[16]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T08:02:33.747Z",codex-sdk-agent,"Scope alignment evidence: PR #431 review caught that the target-surface body omitted append from item facets. Updated the live epic body through pm update so the consolidation grammar includes comments/notes/learnings/files/docs/deps/append/test."
  "2026-07-06T22:23:28.633Z",codex,"Audit evidence 2026-07-06/07 codex: live pm --help still exposes 64+ top-level/user-visible spellings plus extension commands and the internal test-runs-worker command. Existing child set covers list/history/package/lifecycle/calendar/facets/context/ops/aggregate/customization/help/contracts/alias-shim clusters. Duplicate-safe search found no focused item for the internal worker leakage, so pm-lp4j was created under this epic. This is a simplification gap only; no runtime feature is removed."
  "2026-07-06T22:31:27.154Z",codex-agent,"Planning evidence 2026-07-06/07 codex-agent: live contracts expose 101 command paths and 59 top-level spellings before consolidation. Existing child partition still covers the simplification strategy: ADR pm-pbyu, token baseline pm-a22j, alias shim pm-0z7n, list/history/package/lifecycle/calendar/facet/context/ops/aggregate/customization clusters, tiered help pm-e2bq, contracts/docs generation pm-mu8m, and internal-worker leakage pm-lp4j. Recommended planning stance: accept the ADR first, land alias shim second, then migrate one cluster at a time with spelling-parity tests and zero feature loss; do not remove any old spelling until hidden aliases and migration hints are test-gated."
  "2026-07-08T16:41:53.189Z",claude-code-agent,"Bundle evidence: contracts --summary provides a cheap top-level command grammar bootstrap for progressive disclosure before agents request command-scoped flags."
  "2026-07-08T17:07:59.070Z",claude-code-agent,"Verification evidence: full coverage passed at 100/100/100/100 (5462 tests), lint/static/docs/contracts gates passed, and packed-install temp proof passed in /tmp/pm-agent-ux-proof-TYSgf1 for pm list --today, pm list --recent, pm contracts --summary, and SDK runAction({action:'contracts', options:{summary:true}})."
  "2026-07-08T17:41:49.351Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update: CI Gates (static) failed because the committed contract snapshot was generated before rebuilding dist after tool-parameter metadata copy changes. Rebuilt with pnpm build, regenerated with pnpm contracts:update, and reran the full static CI sequence locally: pnpm version:check && pnpm changelog:pm:check && pnpm contracts:check && pnpm security:scan && pnpm lint && npm pack --dry-run. Result: passed."
  "2026-07-08T18:04:30.464Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence: addressed latest bot feedback before repush. Fixed SDK/MCP search contract leakage by keeping list-only --today/--recent out of search schemas, added help to contracts summary intents, treated programmatic updatedAfter:null as unselected, and clarified open-only today docs. Verification passed: focused tests (78 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5463 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T18:23:03.452Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed the final Gemini normalizer finding by making normalizeExtensionFlagName accept unknown, ignore null/blank values, trim valid strings, and reject non-string values with a deterministic TypeError. Added focused coverage. Verification passed: focused tests (79 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5464 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T18:49:40.069Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed final Gemini edge cases by ignoring blank updatedAfter values in list window conflict detection and adding more core command intents (guide, ops, reindex, focus, telemetry) to contracts summary output. Verification passed: focused tests (79 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5464 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T19:17:16.701Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed CodeRabbit schema feedback by expanding the shared summary parameter description to include health rollups and adding contracts action schema mutual-exclusion rules for projection flags. Verification passed: focused tests (80 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5465 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T19:39:00.993Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed Greptile pushed-review schema/runtime mismatch by adding action-schema mutual-exclusion rules for list today/recent/updatedAfter windows across list variants. Verification passed: focused tests (81 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5466 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T20:07:39.770Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed final value-sensitive schema feedback by making schema mutual exclusion conditional on selected boolean values, adding completion summary intent, and rejecting bare '-' short extension flags. Verification passed: focused tests (81 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5466 tests)."
  "2026-07-13T21:41:29.812Z",codex-root,"Command-surface audit 2026-07-13: the live root help advertises 67 subcommands. They partition into history 6, list/query 9, item facets 8, package-owned governance/audit 6, claim lifecycle 4, close lifecycle 4, package lifecycle 4, context 3, calendar sugar 3, operations 7, stable remaining core 12, and one internal worker leak. Existing children already cover the consolidation work, so no duplicate simplification items were created. Proposed target remains a small noun-oriented grammar with status filters replacing list aliases, item facets grouped under item, lifecycle actions grouped consistently, package/extension commands grouped under package, and extension-owned audit commands discoverable without polluting the core surface. Preserve every capability, stable machine-readable contracts, shell composability, and compact default output."
  "2026-07-13T22:09:18.183Z",codex-root,"Relationship organization 2026-07-13: agent story pm-1kxs now has blocked_by edges to all 15 active command-grammar delivery clusters required by its acceptance criteria: alias foundation, tiered help, list/history/package/lifecycle/calendar/bulk/navigation/facets/ops/aggregate/customization consolidation, internal-worker hiding, and contract-generated adapters/docs. Metrics-only pm-0mox remains non-blocking. This records the complete delivery graph without creating any duplicate simplification item."
  "2026-07-15T20:06:34.985Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Review pass 91 agent-UX evidence: pm plan create executes as a positional action, but pm plan create --help --json returns unknown_command while pm plan --help advertises create and the help model exposes no subcommands. Focused issue pm-2tan was added under the command/help lineage to unify action help, contracts, and completion without broadening this umbrella."
  "2026-07-21T15:56:01.477Z",codex-tracker-governance,"Live command-surface planning 2026-07-21: root help exposes 75 top-level names while contracts summary exposes 63 canonical summaries. The partition remains complete with zero feature loss: list variants -> pm-pfqi; history and restore family -> pm-tqel; package lifecycle -> pm-tnud; lifecycle sugar -> pm-eq4x; calendar sugar -> pm-o3fh; bulk/destructive -> pm-ik19; navigation/context -> pm-kcs4; item facets -> pm-yql1; diagnostics -> pm-6apl; aggregate -> pm-xkgq; customization -> pm-npr3. pm-lp4j owns test-runs-worker visibility and pm-szdc owns completion helper visibility. item, graph, merge, plan, package, schema, config, and history are noun-verb exemplars, not new leaks. Sequence remains decision pm-pbyu, alias substrate pm-0z7n, independent cluster migrations, tiered help pm-e2bq, generated contracts/docs pm-mu8m, then token regression proof pm-cu1i."
notes[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T04:55:44.581Z",maintainer-agent,"Brainstorm census 2026-07-05 — current surface is ~60 top-level commands. Redundancy clusters found; 8 list-* status variants (list/all/draft/open/in-progress/blocked/closed/canceled), 5 history-family commands (history/history-redact/history-repair/history-compact/activity) plus restore, 4 package-lifecycle commands (extension/package/install/upgrade — extension and package are already partial synonyms), 3 lifecycle sugar commands (start-task/pause-task/close-task) duplicating claim/release/close+status, 3 calendar shortcuts (meet/event/remind) duplicating create with presets, 6 diagnostics commands (stats/health/validate/gc/telemetry/eval). Consolidating just these clusters removes ~24 top-level entries with zero feature loss."
  "2026-07-05T04:55:44.951Z",maintainer-agent,"Sequencing decision — alias shim layer (pm-0z7n) is the shared foundation and must land first after ADR pm-pbyu acceptance; each cluster task then becomes a mechanical table edit + spelling-parity spec. Token baseline (pm-a22j) runs before any change so the epic has measurable before/after evidence. Every rename must walk the full wiring checklist (commands/index, register-mutation, mcp/server, sdk/cli-contracts, contracts.ts, completions x3 shells, docs, vitest.config, contracts:update)."
  "2026-07-06T08:04:41.835Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-06 audit #7 (third pass): live top-level surface measured at 64 commands (pm --help). All previously-filed clusters still map 1:1 to children. Two unmapped spellings found and resolved by note/comment (no new items needed): 'aggregate' -> proposed as a pm list projection flag (query-read family, see ADR comment on pm-pbyu); 'test-all' -> ops verb, scope note added to pm-6apl. 'beads' and 'changelog' are package-owned commands and already conform to grammar rule 4 (sugar/package-provided, not core surface). New child added: pm-vxxm (GH-442 contracts --summary) — the contracts-side tier of the token-cost AC. Fresh dogfood evidence quantifying the epic's motivation now tracked under pm-mpbb: pm-cfed (JSON +48-53% vs TOON), pm-nilh (mutation echo 12.7x), pm-ishm (43% of context = repeated tags), pm-g9xk (constant error boilerplate)."
  "2026-07-06T23:10:33.100Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-07 grammar re-verification + brainstorm additions. Live surface counted from pm --help: 65 top-level commands (63 core + 2 extension groups beads/changelog). Every core spelling maps to exactly one consolidation child (pm-pfqi list-*, pm-tqel history family, pm-tnud package family, pm-eq4x lifecycle sugar, pm-o3fh calendar sugar, pm-ik19 bulk/destructive, pm-kcs4 navigation, pm-yql1 annotation facets incl. test/test-all, pm-6apl ops, pm-xkgq aggregate, pm-npr3 customization family, pm-lp4j internal worker) — partition still complete, no new top-level command has leaked in since the last pass. New brainstorm points: (1) fix a SHARED VERB VOCABULARY across nouns so agents can guess subcommands (proposal commented on ADR pm-pbyu); (2) future query-power features must land as flags on existing nouns, never new nouns — filed pm-plwm (--where predicates) with that constraint stated in its AC; (3) tie the done-definition to the pm-a22j token baseline: target pm --help fitting one screen and contracts --summary (pm-vxxm) as the default agent bootstrap path."
  "2026-07-18T05:46:18.034Z",maintainer-agent,"Live grammar exemplar recorded 2026-07-18: `pm graph` (PR#580/#581) is the first large post-census command family shipped natively in the target noun-verb shape — ONE top-level noun with 12 verbs (neighbors/paths/closure/impact/subgraph/audit/profile/analyze/communities/redundancy/dominators/plan), subcommand enum single-sourced in sdk/cli-contracts/enum-contracts.ts, thin 7-line CLI shim (cli/graph.ts), one MCP tool. Net top-level surface cost of an entire graph platform: +1 command. This is the concrete before/after argument for the pbyu decision and the consolidation children (pfqi list-*, tqel history, tnud package, eq4x lifecycle): each cluster collapses N spellings to one noun exactly like graph. Also the counter-pressure evidence: every new first-class MCP tool costs ~+500 cold-start tokens (measurement on pm-9k90), so consolidation + profiles beat tool-count growth."
  "2026-07-18T14:08:36.887Z",codex-ecosystem-planner,"2026-07-18 live command-surface census and complete partition review: root help exposes 73 names. User capability still partitions without loss into the existing noun families: list variants -> pm-pfqi; history/activity/restore/repair/redact/compact -> pm-tqel; package/extension/install/upgrade -> pm-tnud; update-many/close-many/delete/test-all -> pm-ik19; context/next/focus -> pm-kcs4; comments/notes/learnings/files/docs/deps/append/test -> pm-yql1; meet/event/remind -> pm-o3fh; start/pause/close-task -> pm-eq4x; stats/health/validate/gc/telemetry/eval -> pm-6apl; aggregate -> pm-xkgq; init/config/schema/profile -> pm-npr3. graph is the conforming noun-verb exemplar; beads/changelog/copy/guide are extension-owned surfaces; completion is the public completion noun. Internal leakage is now fully owned by pm-lp4j for test-runs-worker and new pm-szdc for completion-statuses/completion-tags/completion-types. Delivery sequence remains pbyu decision -> 0z7n alias substrate -> cluster migrations, while e2bq + mu8m + lp4j + szdc independently shrink and single-source discovery. No other command lacks a canonical target."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T04:55:45.356Z",maintainer-agent,Surface growth pattern learned from history; features were added as new top-level commands because that was the path of least resistance in Commander registration — the grammar ADR plus contracts-generated help removes that incentive by making subcommand addition cheaper than top-level addition.
  "2026-07-06T08:04:42.231Z",maintainer-agent,"Dogfood measurements (2026-07-05 external agent audit, GH-435/437/442/443/445) put hard numbers on the simplification thesis: bootstrap costs ~25KB (pm contracts) before the first real command; per-loop costs are dominated by output shape (full-item mutation echoes 12.7x over --id-only; tags 43% of pm context; JSON +48-53% over TOON). Consolidating the grammar (this epic) fixes discovery cost; the pm-mpbb lean-output cluster fixes loop cost. Both are needed to hit the agent token-cost AC."
