  README.md,project,README badge metadata touched during final verification bundle
body: "## Charter\nReduce cognitive surface, not capability. The pm CLI keeps 100% of its features but presents them behind a small noun-verb grammar. This epic is the umbrella for the brainstormed consolidation clusters (each a child item) and the ADR that fixes the grammar rules.\n\n## Grammar principles (brainstorm summary — ADR child formalizes)\n1. Noun-first: one top-level command per domain noun (item lifecycle, list, history, package, schema, config, profile, plan, search, ops/diagnostics).\n2. Verbs/facets are subcommands or flags, never new top-level commands.\n3. Status/type projections are flags (--status, --type), not command variants.\n4. Sugar commands (shortcuts, lifecycle aliases) are hidden aliases or package-provided, never core surface.\n5. Nothing is deleted: every current spelling keeps working via an alias shim that prints a one-line migration hint (suppressible via config).\n6. Contracts are the source of truth: help tiers, completions, MCP tools, and docs are all generated from the same contract table.\n\n## Target surface (~15 nouns)\ninit, config, schema, profile, package (extension/install/upgrade), create (+meet/event/remind sugar), get, list (all status variants), update (update-many), close (close-many/delete), claim (release/start/pause), item facets (comments/notes/learnings/files/docs/deps/append/test), history (restore/redact/repair/compact/activity), search, plan, context (next/focus), ops (stats/health/validate/gc/telemetry/eval), contracts, help.\n\n## Relationship to SDK-first epic\nConsolidation is implemented on top of the SDK-first primitives (see linked epic under pm-ugqx): command shims become thin SDK calls, which is what makes the alias layer cheap and regression-safe.\n\n## Cluster index update (review 2026-07-05, second pass)\nThree target-surface clusters previously had no implementing child; filed: pm-yql1 (item annotation facets), pm-ik19 (bulk/destructive lifecycle variants), pm-kcs4 (context/next/focus navigation noun). ADR pm-pbyu ownership resolution for the earlier mapping conflicts: restore belongs under history because it replays audited history state, while eval belongs under ops because it is a diagnostic/evaluation surface rather than a primary search query primitive.\n\n## Target-surface visibility clarification (2026-07-18)\nThe approximately 15-noun target enumerates canonical user-facing capability families, not every compatibility, bulk, or internal spelling. Public pm completion remains a discoverable optional package-owned noun for generating bash, zsh, and fish scripts. Runtime data providers completion-statuses, completion-tags, and completion-types remain available to those scripts through compatibility or explicit internal plumbing but do not count as public nouns (pm-szdc). test-all remains fully available as a compatibility spelling and is consolidated under the test family as the bulk test --all facet (pm-ik19). No completion or bulk-test functionality is removed."
